Text.Value: I have fought great wars before, in the service of other gods, and other powers. But for Myrkul, I would condemn all of Faer√ªn to death.
You are no True Soul - you are a champion. Kill the madman. I fight at your side.
Perhaps you hoped to learn your place in history before you are erased from it. A bright flash of clarity before the snuffing-out.
There you are. As predicted. What is it, I wonder, that draws one toward death like a moth to light?
I sense you ask questions only to hear yourself answer them - so by all means, tell me my place.
I know my destiny - he's waiting in Baldur's Gate. And you're standing in my way, old man.
Neither you nor your pal Gortash know the first thing about my 'place'.
Good luck in the City of Judgement. I wish you the best, sincerely.
Enough talk. Let's finish this.
For that, he asked that I serve as his Chosen, join Orin and Gortash to grow the cult of the Absolute, and then... take control of it.
With pleasure.
But he did not only give me power - he gave me the one thing no other god could grant me.
Perhaps...
My Lord, I offer you these souls so they may return as servants to your cause.
I'm grateful to you for bringing me home. I was a fool to resist. I know better now.
What good is an army of thralls if they do not obey their master?
I'm here to snuff out this whole evil plot - and you along with it.
Join the army of the dead, True Soul. Witness Lord Myrkul's glory!
Let us speak plainly.
The very fact of your being attests to its power - despite your infection, you resisted the brain, here in the heart of its domain.
He's never had a more devoted follower.
Finer champions than you have tried and failed. But perhaps they lacked the fear that drives you: your freedom, hanging in the balance.
Say farewell, Isobel.
Impossible - you are bound to it, and in death it will bind you to me.
You. After all you've done, after all your trifling, you dare strike at my daughter?!
My place is standing over you, with my boot on your throat.
Repent? Would that even be possible?
You are planning on betraying your allies?
My place is right here - ready to strike you down in Lady Shar's name.
My place is in Baldur's Gate. Yours is in a grave - permanently, this time.
Why is the Prism so important to you?
All mortals find their place at our Lord's side in time - your time is now.
Balthazar - I should have expected his weakness.
You could have run away. Absconded with the Prism - the one thing that could prevent me from fulfilling my destiny.
I only serve one god.
The liberation of my people may be close at hand. And I will stop at nothing to see it done.
My Lord Myrkul gave me the one thing I desired - the one thing that no other god could grant me.
Yes.
And what is my place, Ketheric?
You. After all you've done, after all your trifling, you dare strike at my daughter?!
In your cage, Aylin.

EditorData.NodeContext: Seeing Nightsong for the first time. Normally she'd be overcome, btu the tadpole is making her cold

Text.Value: A temptation or a threat? With your god, it's always the latter, isn't it?
I just want to be free of my parasite.
I will kill you now. And then I will raise you as my servant.
My daughter's life returned. Her heart beating once more.
Funny you say that. My place is right here, and my 'bright flash' could be the last thing you see...
You have an alliance with the Black Hand, Bane. I am his servant. You ought to work with me.
I will continue to serve him on this plane as long as I am needed, for he has given me everything I want.
I am right where I need to be - ready to vanquish you and your curse, forever.
What a fool you are. I am death. She is mine. She will return - always return. And you...
For a moment - a moment only - I was weak. No longer.
Damned wretch. I will liberate my father from your rotten hands.
I am not intimidated by the likes of you. I will gain my queen's favour and ascend.
Isobel - my love, what has happened to you?

EditorData.NodeContext: Seeing isobel for the first time - shock and surprise, and horror that she's been tadpoled

Text.Value: There you are. As predicted. What is it, I wonder, that draws one toward death like a moth to light?
That is the power my Lord Myrkul has granted me - command over the immeasurable legions of the dead.
I was ready to show you mercy before. It's still not too late. You can repent.
Your place is to die so I might finally live.
I will find out who I was, and end my killing fate.
But the lure of one's destiny is irresistible, isn't it?
You are all that stands between me and my destiny - and you have brought the Prism here.
You - what in the name of the Nine Hells are you doing here?!

Text.Value: My place is at the Lord of Bones' side, like yours.
I will reach my own crimson castle, and your corpse will pave my path.
You - what in the name of the Nine Hells are you doing here?!

Text.Value: Join the army of the dead, True Soul. Witness Lord Myrkul's glory!
A mad dog like Orin might be impressed. I am not.
But the lure of one's destiny is irresistible, isn't it?

Synopsis: This dialog plays at the start of the Ketheric boss fight in the Colony. There are numerous permutations here: Nightsong being dead or alive, freed from her soul cage (through stealth before being spotted); Isobel being absent or tadpoled or tadpoled and killed (in the boss chamber) before entering the dialog; Jaheira being present here (and spotted) or being absent.
